<HEADLINE>
FT  25 JUN 92 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
In the closing week of the Australian sales a relatively large offering of
172,000 bales is being auctioned at Sydney, Melbourne and Fremantle. The
easier tendency of recnt weeks continued on Monday and Tuesday, with a high
proportion being passed in up to 33 per cent in Sydney. However, prices
improved on Wednesday at all three centres, particularly for fine merino
fleece of good style. Japan has been buying strongly, and Chinese interest
in the market is thought to have been an important factor. The AWC market
indicator after falling to 539, rose three cents a kg to 542 compared with
561 a week ago.
</TEXT>
