FT  25 JUN 92 / UK Company News: Courts suffers 11% downturn to Pounds 8.09m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Courts (Furnishers) suffered a fall in pre-tax profits from Pounds 9.05m to
Pounds 8.09m for the year ended March 31, with the trading environment
remaining exceptionally difficult throughout the period.
The 11 per cent downturn in profits was after taking account of interest
charges of Pounds 5.37m (Pounds 5.52m), a transfer to deferred profit of
Pounds 5.31m (Pounds 5.55m) and property disposal losses of Pounds 560,000
(profit Pounds 1.64m). On the plus side there was a Pounds 1.28m share of
profit from the new Trinidad associate.
Earnings worked through at 19.7p (23.8p). A final dividend of 3.17p holds
the total at 5p.
Group turnover increased by 5 per cent to Pounds 184m. The figure excluded
any contribution from the Trinidad associate but included the depreciatory
effects of the 66 per cent devaluation of the Jamaican dollar.
